				<p><p>You just need a DC-DC converter. This will take care of stepping down the voltage from battery to USB power specs. You may buy the ICs online and solder them or look for a breakout boards for quick setup. </p>

<p>Alternatively, you can look for USB car chargers or LiPo BEC (Battery Elimination Circuit). 
You can break open the Car USB charger (which has the cigar lighter mount), and solder the battery leads to those terminals (<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2IOs3g-52Zo" rel="nofollow">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2IOs3g-52Zo</a> , Omit the variable voltage part. You can just use the USB power)</p>

